name: adsensehost
title: AdSense Host API
description: Generates performance reports, generates ad codes, and provides publisher management capabilities for AdSense Hosts.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

fields.name: colors
fields.desc: The colors included in the style. These are represented as six hexadecimal characters, similar to HTML color codes, but without the leading hash.

fields.name: background
fields.desc: The color of the ad background.

fields.name: border
fields.desc: The color of the ad border.

fields.name: text
fields.desc: The color of the ad text.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: The color of the ad title.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: The color of the ad url.

fields.name: corners
fields.desc: The style of the corners in the ad (deprecated: never populated, ignored).

fields.name: font
fields.desc: The font which is included in the style.

fields.name: family
fields.desc: The family of the font. Possible values are: ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_FAMILY, ADSENSE_DEFAULT_FAMILY, ARIAL, TIMES and VERDANA.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: The size of the font. Possible values are: ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_SIZE, ADSENSE_DEFAULT_SIZE, SMALL, MEDIUM and LARGE.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind this is, in this case adsensehost#adStyle.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this ad unit. This should be considered an opaque identifier; it is not safe to rely on it being in any particular format.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adsensehost#adUnit.

fields.name: mobileContentAdsSettings
fields.desc: Settings specific to WAP mobile content ads (AFMC - deprecated).

fields.name: scriptingLanguage
fields.desc: The scripting language to use for this ad unit.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: Size of this ad unit.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Type of this ad unit.

fields.name: markupLanguage
fields.desc: The markup language to use for this ad unit.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of this ad unit.

fields.name: status
fields.desc:
Status of this ad unit. Possible values are:
NEW: Indicates that the ad unit was created within the last seven days and does not yet have any activity associated with it.

ACTIVE: Indicates that there has been activity on this ad unit in the last seven days.

INACTIVE: Indicates that there has been no activity on this ad unit in the last seven days.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Identity code of this ad unit, not necessarily unique across ad clients.

fields.name: contentAdsSettings
fields.desc: Settings specific to content ads (AFC) and highend mobile content ads (AFMC - deprecated).

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Type of this ad unit. Possible values are TEXT, TEXT_IMAGE, IMAGE and LINK.

fields.name: backupOption
fields.desc: The backup option to be used in instances where no ad is available.

fields.name: color
fields.desc: Color to use when type is set to COLOR. These are represented as six hexadecimal characters, similar to HTML color codes, but without the leading hash.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Type of the backup option. Possible values are BLANK, COLOR and URL.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: URL to use when type is set to URL.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: Size of this ad unit. Size values are in the form SIZE_{width}_{height}.

fields.name: customStyle
fields.desc: Custom style information specific to this ad unit.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of this response for caching purposes.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The ad units returned in this list response.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of list this is, in this case adsensehost#adUnits.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Continuation token used to page through ad units. To retrieve the next page of results, set the next request's "pageToken" value to this.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this account.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adsensehost#account.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of this account.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: Approval status of this account. One of: PENDING, APPROVED, DISABLED.

fields.name: supportsReporting
fields.desc: Whether this ad client supports being reported on.

fields.name: arcOptIn
fields.desc: Whether this ad client is opted in to ARC.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this ad client.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adsensehost#adClient.

fields.name: productCode
fields.desc: This ad client's product code, which corresponds to the PRODUCT_CODE report dimension.

fields.name: websiteUrl
fields.desc: The URL of the user's hosted website.

fields.name: productCodes
fields.desc: The products to associate with the user. Options: AFC, AFG, AFV, AFS (deprecated), AFMC (deprecated)

fields.name: redirectUrl
fields.desc: Redirect URL of this association session. Used to redirect users into the AdSense association flow.

fields.name: websiteLocale
fields.desc: The locale of the user's hosted website.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: Status of the completed association, available once the association callback token has been verified. One of ACCEPTED, REJECTED, or ERROR.

fields.name: userLocale
fields.desc: The preferred locale of the user themselves when going through the AdSense association flow.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Hosted account id of the associated publisher after association. Present if status is ACCEPTED.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this association session.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adsensehost#associationSession.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The custom channels returned in this list response.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of list this is, in this case adsensehost#customChannels.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Continuation token used to page through custom channels. To retrieve the next page of results, set the next request's "pageToken" value to this.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of this response for caching purposes.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of list this is, in this case adsensehost#urlChannels.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Continuation token used to page through URL channels. To retrieve the next page of results, set the next request's "pageToken" value to this.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of this response for caching purposes.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The URL channels returned in this list response.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of this response for caching purposes.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The accounts returned in this list response.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of list this is, in this case adsensehost#accounts.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Code of this custom channel, not necessarily unique across ad clients.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this custom channel. This should be considered an opaque identifier; it is not safe to rely on it being in any particular format.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adsensehost#customChannel.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of this custom channel.

fields.name: averages
fields.desc: The averages of the report. This is the same length as any other row in the report; cells corresponding to dimension columns are empty.

fields.name: headers
fields.desc: The header information of the columns requested in the report. This is a list of headers; one for each dimension in the request, followed by one for each metric in the request.

fields.name: currency
fields.desc: The currency of this column. Only present if the header type is METRIC_CURRENCY.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the header.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the header; one of DIMENSION, METRIC_TALLY, METRIC_RATIO, or METRIC_CURRENCY.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind this is, in this case adsensehost#report.

fields.name: rows
fields.desc: The output rows of the report. Each row is a list of cells; one for each dimension in the request, followed by one for each metric in the request. The dimension cells contain strings, and the metric cells contain numbers.

fields.name: totalMatchedRows
fields.desc: The total number of rows matched by the report request. Fewer rows may be returned in the response due to being limited by the row count requested or the report row limit.

fields.name: totals
fields.desc: The totals of the report. This is the same length as any other row in the report; cells corresponding to dimension columns are empty.

fields.name: warnings
fields.desc: Any warnings associated with generation of the report.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this URL channel. This should be considered an opaque identifier; it is not safe to rely on it being in any particular format.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adsensehost#urlChannel.

fields.name: urlPattern
fields.desc: URL Pattern of this URL channel. Does not include "http://" or "https://". Example: www.example.com/home

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of this response for caching purposes.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The ad clients returned in this list response.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of list this is, in this case adsensehost#adClients.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Continuation token used to page through ad clients. To retrieve the next page of results, set the next request's "pageToken" value to this.

fields.name: adCode
fields.desc: The ad code snippet.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind this is, in this case adsensehost#adCode.

methods.name: generate
methods.desc: Generate an AdSense report based on the report request sent in the query parameters. Returns the result as JSON; to retrieve output in CSV format specify "alt=csv" as a query parameter.

pathParams.name: accountId
pathParams.desc: Hosted account upon which to report.

requiredQueryParams.name: startDate
requiredQueryParams.desc: Start of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.

requiredQueryParams.name: endDate
requiredQueryParams.desc: End of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.

optinalQueryParams.name: filter
optinalQueryParams.desc: Filters to be run on the report.

optinalQueryParams.name: locale
optinalQueryParams.desc: Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local language. Defaults to "en_US" if not specified.

optinalQueryParams.name: startIndex
optinalQueryParams.desc: Index of the first row of report data to return.

optinalQueryParams.name: dimension
optinalQueryParams.desc: Dimensions to base the report on.

optinalQueryParams.name: maxResults
optinalQueryParams.desc: The maximum number of rows of report data to return.

optinalQueryParams.name: metric
optinalQueryParams.desc: Numeric columns to include in the report.

optinalQueryParams.name: sort
optinalQueryParams.desc: The name of a dimension or metric to sort the resulting report on, optionally prefixed with "+" to sort ascending or "-" to sort descending. If no prefix is specified, the column is sorted ascending.
